articles.title: Antarctic sea-ice at 'mind-blowing' low alarms experts - BBC
articles.description: Missing winter sea-ice signals changes in Antarctica that could be "absolute disaster for the world", scientists say.
articles.content:
The sea-ice surrounding Antarctica is well below any previous recorded winter level, satellite data shows, a worrying new benchmark for a region that once seemed resistant to global warming.
